quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,52,"But it is not except a reminder to the worlds."
  69,49,"And indeed, We know that among you are deniers."
  69,50,"And indeed, it will be [a cause of] regret upon the disbelievers."
  69,51,"And indeed, it is the truth of certainty."
  70,43,"The Day they will emerge from the graves rapidly as if they were, toward an erected idol, hastening.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., just as they used to race, whenever an idol was newly appointed, to be the first of its worshippers.
  70,44,"Their eyes humbled, humiliation will cover them. That is the Day which they had been promised."
  74,28,"It lets nothing remain and leaves nothing [unburned],"
  74,29,"Altering [i.e., blackening] the skins."
  74,30,"Over it are nineteen [angels]."
  75,25,"Expecting that there will be done to them [something] backbreaking."
  75,26,"No! When it [i.e., the soul] has reached the collar bones{1}",footnotes:1:At the time it is about to leave the body when one is on the verge of death.
  75,27,"And it is said, "
  76,19,"There will circulate among them young boys made eternal. When you see them, you would think them [as beautiful as] scattered pearls."
  76,20,"And when you look there [in Paradise], you will see pleasure and great dominion."
  76,21,"Upon them [i.e., the inhabitants] will be green garments of fine silk and brocade. And they will be adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a purifying drink."
  77,16,"Did We not destroy the former peoples?"
  77,17,"Then We will follow them with the later ones."
  77,18,"Thus do We deal with the criminals."
  78,13,"And made [therein] a burning lamp"
  78,14,"And sent down, from the rain clouds, pouring water."
  78,15,"That We may bring forth thereby grain and vegetation."
  79,7,"There will follow it the subsequent [one]."
  79,8,"Hearts,{1} that Day, will tremble,",footnotes:1:Those of the disbelievers who denied the Resurrection.
  79,9,"Their eyes{1} humbled.",footnotes:1:Those of the disbelievers.
  80,4,"Or be reminded and the remembrance would benefit him?"
  80,5,"As for he who thinks himself without need,{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., without need of faith or need of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) . Here it is in reference to a certain influential member of the Quraysh whom the Prophet (ﷺ) had hoped to bring to Islām.
  80,6,"To him you give attention."
  81,1,"When the sun is wrapped up [in darkness]"
  81,2,"And when the stars fall, dispersing,"
  81,3,"And when the mountains are removed"